11. mv "old name" "new name" it's the command to change the name of file/folder ect...
                                                        DOCKERS

1.docker run -v /var/test:/var/test -p 8080:8080 name or id docker image
2.docker rm -f "namy or id container" - to stop running the container
3.docker images - to show all available images
4.docker ibspect id/name  - to show all info about conteiner
5.docker-compose up    - to run compose file (-d make the process hidden)
6.docker-compose ps  - to show running images


                                                      Git

1.git clone "link to relevant repo from github" - to copy relevant repo to local mashine
2.git status - show status of files.difference between original repo and added files
3.git add . - adds files that we want to send to github.these files must be in the same location as original repo.if not we must indicate the direction
3-a. git rm --cached "name of wanted file" or . for all attached files. this command unttached from git selected files.
If we changed tracked(after add command) files we have to put "git add ." command again.
4.git commit -m "freetext" 
5.git push origin main -  to push to our github
6. git branch - show which branch we belong
7.git branch "name" create a new branch
8.git branch -D "name" delete the branch
9. git checkout "name" - switch to selected branch
10.git checkout -b "name"  -  create and switch to new branch
11.git merge "name" - merge currently branch with selected
12.git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
   git config --global user.name "Your Name"        
two commands for credentials to git hub

                                                        SSH

For connection between machines(server-client) we need to create/generate Key on the server machine
1. enter/enter/enter 
2.This command create 2 keys in location /home/ubuntu/.ssh : 1. id_rsa it's private key and him have to stay here allways
                                                             2. id_rsa.pub it's public key  his content we have to copy to remote machine(client) to location:/home/ubuntu/.ssh/authorized_keys
*impotante! if another key already exists on the client then the contens of the desired key must be written under the existing key.



                                                 Ansible

1.ansible-playbook "name of playbook.yaml"   -  to invoke the playbook of ansible
2./etc/ansible/hosts    - here we have to define all locations(ip or dns) that we would like execute ansibles playbook
3.for connections we need to use ssh protocol and to create ssh security key on the main server. the key divided into two key:private and public.
private stay on the main server allways .public we copy to all locations that we want to connect .~/.ssh/authorized_key  is location to there we have to copy public key
4.ansible -m ping all   this command check if our connection is done and good.
answer :3.128.182.172 | SUCCESS => {
    "changed": false,
    "ping": "pong"
}

                                                              Ansible-role

1.ansible-galaxy init "name" to creat role of ansible
2./etc/ansible/roles is default locations of ansible-role if it doesnt exit we have to create 
and exactly there we need to invoke command ansible-galaxy init "name" and system automatecly create all directores
default-variablse
file-variablse constant
task-all modules
test-check if the role done fix
example:
roles:
