                                                   Terraform


1.to install terraform  on windows machine pls following according insruction:
 download relivanty file from terrafon site
 unziping him
 create folder on C/ 
 put the file there
 right click on myPc->propirtes->Advanced system setting->enviroment Variables ->double click on path->create new->put path of installation file-> save
2.to install terraform on ubuntu machine pls following according insruction:
selecte relivanty file from terrafon site
right click on the file, make copy link address
come to terminal of ubuntu and put command wget "link address" ,file zip is download
put command unzip on the file
sudo cp "unziping file" /usr/local/bin/
3. after create terraform file.tf on VS-code we have to put command  "terraform init" in terminal
exactly where the file.tf located
put command "terraform plan" just to check what terraform gonna create or change
put command "terraform apply"  we confirm about changes
value:yes

if we want to remove all created itemes
put command:"terraform destroy
yes
put command "terraform state list" show all resource that we created
put command "terraform destroy -target "name of instance" " delete specifical iteims

terraform.tfvars this is saved name of the file on system there we put all value of the variables
if we put values into file that his name isn"t terraform.tfvars system doesn"t can call the values we need to put name of the file into comand line
example: name of the file of values - values
commnad line - terraform plan/apply -var-file= values

type of avalibales values on terraform:
1-string
2-boolean
3-list      example via command line:terraform plan/apply -var 'vpc_cidr_block=["10.0.0.0/16,"10.20.0.0/16]' here we send 2 values to variable vpc_cidr_block
4-map (key->value)    example via command line:plan/apply -var 'name of variable={name of key="name of value"}'
----
to sent request to AWS about all vpc existing and print them: data "aws_vpcs" "free name value"{
}
output "vpcs" {
value = data.awc_vpcs.name of value
}
----
 way to add PairKey to attach the key to created instances:

   resource "aws_instance" "my_ubuntu" {
   #count of instances that will create 
    count = 2
    ami = "ami-0932440befd74cdba"
    instance_type = "t2.micro"
    user_data = file ("user_data")
    vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.MyFirstSG.id]
    key_name="MyPairKey2"     # here we put name of existing  pair key
}
#######Create new EC2 key pair########
    resource "tls_private_key" "this" {
    algorithm = "RSA"
    }

    module "key_pair" {
    source = "terraform-aws-modules/key-pair/aws"

    key_name   = "deployer-one"
    public_key = tls_private_key.this.public_key_openssh
}





